public class DefaultProInflammatoryCytokine<T extends NervousSystemElement> extends AbstractCytokine<T>
Implementation of a pro-inflammatory cytokine in the nervous system. Represents a cytokine that targets various elements of the nervous system to induce inflammatory responses.

This class extends AbstractCytokine and provides specific behavior for interacting with different types of targets.

To extend this class:

  • Ensure the constructor properly initializes inherited fields.
  • Override methods to provide specific behavior if needed.
  • Document the purpose of any new methods or overridden methods.
  • Use super to call the superclass method when overriding to extend or modify its behavior.

  • Method Details

    • interactWithTarget

      public void interactWithTarget()
      Interacts with the target to induce an inflammatory response.

      If the target is a neuron, it will either reduce myelin or delete a mitochondrion. If the target is an astrocyte, it will be deactivated. If the target is another microglia, it will produce more cytokines. Interacts with the target element, potentially altering its state or behavior.
